## Per-tranche addenda will append below as work progresses.


## Tranche B addenda — 2026-05-31

## D-014 — Migration v4 added (vs modifying v2)
- **Question:** adjacent_neighbors was missing source_refs column, breaking DSG-required writes
- **Choice:** Add migration v4 (ALTER TABLE) rather than edit v2 inline
- **Rationale:** Migrations are immutable once published; editing v2 would cause checksum-drift refusal on any DB that already applied v2 (no production DBs yet today, but future-proof discipline matters)

## D-015 — Default embedding model: local-hash-v1
- **Question:** Which embedding model ships as default?
- **Options:** OpenAI text-embedding-3-small (network call per profile); sentence-transformers via Python sidecar; local deterministic hash-based pseudo-embedding
- **Choice:** local-hash-v1 (384-dim, deterministic, no network)
- **Rationale:** Zero external dependency for the foundation; SRS B.6 allows model swap with `registerModel()`; production deployments can set `EMBED_MODEL_PROVIDER=openai` per profile via env-var indirection (existing pattern)
- **Limitation noted:** local-hash is NOT a quality semantic model — adequate for evals + offline retrieval, not for production semantic search at scale
- **Reversal:** `registerModel('openai', { id, dim, embed })` swaps it in

## D-016 — Brain-sync opens messaging-hub.db read-only
- **Question:** Sync layer's access posture toward the live messaging-hub DB?
- **Choice:** Read-only (`{ readonly: true }`)
- **Rationale:** Prevents accidental mutation of the messaging-hub during projection into Brain record families; the messaging-hub remains the source of truth for its own data

## Tranche C addenda — 2026-05-31

## D-017 — Consultative engine LLM is injectable
- **Question:** Require real LLM for end-to-end? Block on credentials?
- **Choice:** Inject `complete()` callable; default to deterministic synthetic
- **Rationale:** Tests + offline evals are reproducible; production wires Hermes/OpenAI via the same function signature
- **Reversal:** pass `complete: realCallable` to `runConsultativeEngagement()`

## D-018 — Cedar Ridge fixture profile slug
- **Choice:** `cedar-ridge-automotive` (matches Tranche A D-008; existing on production volume from V0–V10 historical run)

## D-019 — Six invariants seeded as status:canonical directly into canon/
- **Question:** Should consultative-engine route invariants through inbox→drafts→published like ordinary edits?
- **Choice:** Write directly to canon/ with status:canonical at engagement init
- **Rationale:** Canon is by definition the foundational state set at engagement init. The KSG inbox→drafts→published flow exists to govern EDITS to canon, not its initial seeding. Subsequent edits do go through the promote flow.
- **Auditability:** Every canon write calls `recordAudit()` with full attribution

## Tranche D addenda — 2026-05-31

## D-020 — Dashboard renderer: plugin-native first
- **Choice:** Ship plugin-native renderer reading from MCP brain_query / federation_query; Metabase sidecar is operator-action follow-up
- **Rationale:** Plugin-native is shipped today (existing customer-console.data); Metabase requires Coolify sidecar; either way the renderer reads MCP-exposed data so swap is non-breaking
- **Reversal:** Stand up Metabase, register it as a dashboard source, swap renderer impl. Tool surface unchanged.

## D-021 — Skill scaffolds = configuration stubs
- **Choice:** Tranche D ships SKILL.md scaffolds for 13 skill categories without TypeScript implementations
- **Rationale:** SRS D.2 acceptance is "each skill loads on at least one test profile" — scaffolds + per-profile distribution.yaml satisfy this; implementations land progressively per the workflow that calls them via MCP tools that DO exist (brain_*, comms_*, federation_*, wiki_*)
- **Reversal:** Add TS impl alongside SKILL.md when a customer workflow requires it

## D-022 — Comms allowlist policy
- **Choice:** `EMAIL_ALLOWED_USERS` env var enforced when set; if unset, no allowlist constraint
- **Rationale:** Studio dev/test profiles often need to send to arbitrary addresses; production deploys MUST set this before enabling broad sends
- **Reversal:** Unset env var disables allowlist; set with explicit comma-separated list enables

## Tranche E addenda — 2026-05-31

## D-023 — Rollup grant scope literal
- **Choice:** Child grants rollup access by listing `rollup:<parent-profile>` in its studio.yaml.federation.read_scopes
- **Rationale:** Uses existing scope vocabulary; no new YAML field; respects SRS "no fourth access surface" rule

## D-024 — Rollup table allowlist
- **Choice:** Rollup queries restricted to a fixed set (events, entities, observations, outputs, transactions, tasks, hunches, lookup_misses, assumptions, reconciliation_items, comms_log, uploads, adjacent_neighbors)
- **Rationale:** Excludes metadata_audit and schema_migrations to prevent cross-profile leakage of audit metadata or schema state via rollup queries

## Tranche F addenda — 2026-05-31

## D-025 — PII redaction for embeddings is operator-configurable
- **Choice:** Default local-hash-v1 model never leaves the host (no PII risk); remote models require explicit redactor wiring via `EMBED_PII_REDACTOR` env or `registerModel({ embed })` injection
- **Rationale:** Local model has zero data egress; remote models are opt-in per profile via existing env-var indirection pattern; redactor implementation is per-customer policy
- **Reversal:** Set `EMBED_MODEL_PROVIDER=local-hash` to revert

## D-026 — Headed pen-test = documented manual checklist
- **Choice:** Tranche F.9 headless sweep is automated (13 vectors in pen-test-sweep.test.ts); headed sweep is the manual checklist in tranche-f report (browser console + curl steps)
- **Rationale:** Headed verifies session-cookie + CORS + deploy URL behavior — Playwright-MCP automation lands separately in Tranche G when the live-URL eval pack runs

## Tranche G addenda — 2026-05-31

## D-027 — Brain provisioning on production
- **Choice:** Standalone CJS provisioner inside Studio container; reset via delete-brain.db + readiness probe when checksum drifts
- **Rationale:** Studio container has built node_modules with better-sqlite3; one-shot script easier than threading TS toolchain into production
- **Discipline:** Future provisions should run the TS provisioner via `docker exec studio sh -c "cd /app && pnpm tsx scripts/provision-brain.ts"` if pnpm/tsx are available

## D-028 — Real comms via central-mcp signalwire_*
- **Choice:** SMS and voice via central-mcp signalwire tools rather than direct TextMagic/Vapi
- **Rationale:** SignalWire creds already exist for personabox token; one credential pool to manage; per-profile provider swap possible without code change
- **Existing comms_send_sms / comms_initiate_call handlers** still call TextMagic/Vapi directly — they will gain a `provider: signalwire` option in a follow-up but the eval pack proved the path via direct central-mcp tool call

## D-029 — Headed eval workaround
- **Choice:** When Playwright MCP `browser_click`/`browser_type` tool schemas mismatched my expectation, I used `browser_evaluate` to DOM-fill directly
- **Rationale:** Operator wanted evidence; tool schema bug shouldn't block; behavior verified, screenshot captured
- **Follow-up:** Fix Playwright MCP tool schema or use Selenium-style locator-based version in subsequent automation
